Unchanged Impact to our thesis
Meaningful Upside Financial results versus consensus
Source: Company data, Morgan Stanley Research

Initial View \((= / + )\) : Recall we exited LQ incrementally positive on our Equal- weight rating, as we observed clear parallels between VSCo's current strategic initiatives & those that have driven other successful turnarounds (such as ANF, GAP, RL, & TPR) (more here). While 1) the 2Q results to us represent another positive datapoint in VSCo's turnaround trajectory, & 2) reiterated FY EBIT/EPS guidance against 2Q outperformance diminishes the previous FY EPS risk we cautioned, this is balanced by 3) our still- limited conviction in a positive EPS revision path & steady- state growth/profitability profile considering 2H macro uncertainty & a still- early- days turnaround (which can prove lengthy & non- linear). That keeps our Equal- weight rating broadly intact, with our estimates & PT under review.

2Q25 (+): VSCo delivered an across- the- board EPS beat to both consensus expectations & mgmt. guidance (33c vs. Street 11c & guidance O- 15c). Sales & GM outperformance were notable, which mgmt. primarily attributed to 1) store traffic outpacing the broader mall, 2) a sequential topline improvement throughout the quarter, 3) strong full- price selling, 4) growth in average transaction size & AUR, & 5) continued pullback in traditional promotions (particularly in the Semi- Annual Sale). We view the print as a positive datapoint for the turnaround, where we had already grown more constructive LQ (more here) - especially mgmt. comments around 1) core intimates improvement, 2) PINK apparel momentum, 3) ongoing Beauty strength, & 4) intentionally reduced discounting activity. That said, aggregate results remain challenged, as evidenced by the business' \(\sim 4\%\) 2Q25 EBIT margin. This is well below VSCo's historical levels, & as noted above, to us leaves the business' steady- state growth & profitability profile still highly uncertain.

3Q25 Guidance \((= / + )\) : VSCo set initial 3Q25 EPS guidance below the Street - similar to others in our coverage & its recent guidance trend (- 75c to - 55c vs. Street - 56c). This guidance reflects 1) better- than- consensus revenue growth (+4% y/y vs. +1%) - which mgmt. attributed to 2Q momentum continuing 3QTD, a Fashion- Showing- driven uplift, & a consistent newness cadence, 2) - in- line- with- Street GM, with ongoing promotional favorability y/y (albeit less than 2Q) & B&O leverage offset by tariff headwinds driving a - 80 bps y/y outcome, & 3) higher- than- expected SG&A on strategic marketing spending, store labor investments, & normal wage rate increases (\~\$525M vs. Street \$498M). At first glance, we're 1) a touch skeptical on VSCo's ability to accelerate q/q revenue growth considering A) recent strength appears a nearly industry- wide trend, & B) rising inflation in 2H, but 2) view 3Q25 profitability guidance as a reasonable starting point - with potential tariff- related downside

FY Guidance \((= / + )\) : VSCO raised FY revenue guidance beyond Street expectations, but reiterated FY EBIT/EPS guidance at levels \(\sim\) in- line with consensus forecasts \((+2\% y / y,\) \\$270- 320M, & \\$1.80- 2.20 vs. Street - flat, \\$292M, & \\$1.92). Mgmt. 1) attributed its more constructive 2H topline outlook vs. 3M ago to 2Q momentum (which has continued 3QTD; 2H \(+3\%\) y/y vs. \(+1\%\) prior & 1H \(+1\%\) ), & 2) noted no profitability/EPS flow- through of 2Q outperformance due to higher incremental tariffs, which entirely offsets a stronger fundamental outlook. Similar to our initial view on 3Q25 guidance, we wonder if revised FY topline guidance proves optimistic, but think FY profitability/EPS guidance is reasonable - similar to our pre- print view (more here).

Stock Reaction (- ): Although VSCO traded as high as \(+10\%\) initially, the stock faded throughout the day to - MSD %. We attribute this reversal to the fact that, despite 2Q outperformance & a more de- risked '25e guide than prior, the market seemingly has limited appetite to underwrite a turnaround story into a volatile 2H backdrop - even with initial proof points.
Our estimates & price target are under review.
